cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Cambium"
message: >-
  If you use this software in your research, please cite it using
  the metadata in this file. Also include an AI Use Statement
  (AI_USE_STATEMENT.md) in your deliverable per the governance policy.
type: software
version: "1.4"
date-released: "2026-06-25"
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  A portable Claude project that acts as a full research institution:
  45 specialized agents across 11 councils spanning the complete lifecycle
  from RFP intake and grant-proposal drafting through code-verified
  results to reports and decks. Human-in-the-loop at 8 mandatory gates;
  governed by an explicit, CI-enforced AI-use policy (authorship,
  IRB, FERPA, dual-use, data sovereignty). Field-agnostic via
  parameterized faculty configuration.
authors:
  - name: "M. Jaslam (University of Idaho · Intermountain Forestry Cooperative)"
    alias: "jpjaslamagrico"
keywords:
  - artificial intelligence
  - research automation
  - multi-agent systems
  - grant writing
  - research lifecycle
  - human-in-the-loop
  - AI governance
  - Claude
  - research integrity
repository-code: "https://github.com/IFC-UIDAHO/Cambium_AI"
url: "https://github.com/IFC-UIDAHO/Cambium_AI"
